For {= facility_project =}+ U.S. food-distribution facility projects publicly announced, opened, completed, or substantially expanded during {= target_period =}, cover each of the {= evidence_side =} evidence sides below with a source (i.e. {= url =}+ URL for each side).

Eligible projects include broadline or specialty foodservice distributor facilities, grocery or retail food distribution centers, and food-focused cold-chain storage/distribution facilities. Generic parcel or e-commerce 3PL projects, pharma-only or other non-food cold-chain projects, retail stores, and pure manufacturing plants are outside scope unless the cited project is explicitly a distribution, warehouse, or cold-storage facility.

The evidence sides of interest, which we refer to as `evidence_side`, are:
- `operator_side`: a page controlled by the facility operator, owner, parent company, OpCo, or another official channel for the operator side of the project.
- `independent_side`: a non-operator page that corroborates the same facility project from a separate source, such as local news, economic-development or government material, chamber material, construction/trade coverage, or contractor/engineering case-study coverage.

Parent-company pages are eligible only when they explicitly tie the OpCo or facility operator to the claimed project. Distinct phases or nearby facilities should stay distinct when the locality, facility, or project event differs.

Requirements:
- The page should make its evidence-side role visible: for `operator_side`, operator/owner/parent/OpCo official control; for `independent_side`, non-operator authorship or publication independent from the operator.
- The page must identify the named operator, owner, or OpCo and tie it to the claimed facility project in the claimed locality.
- The page must show that the project was announced, opened, completed, or substantially expanded during {= target_period =}.
- The page must expose a concrete facility/project detail, such as investment, jobs, square footage, docks, freezer/cooler/dry-storage capacity, construction or opening timeline, delivery/cold-chain capability, or comparable operations datum.
